data: Menu People Research Projects Outreach Projects CFPU Home Page Physics Department Observational Cosmology, Gravitational Lensing and Astrophysics The astrophysics and observational cosmology group is active in a variety of projects involving the study of galaxy clusters, individual galaxies, sheets and voids in the galaxy distribution, and large-scale structure in general. The fundamental links between all these lines of research are that they provide clues to the nature of the dark matter and energy as well as measuring the fundamental parameters of cosmology.
